      <b data-is-speakable>In 'Hidden Valley Road', A Family's Journey Helps Shift The Science Of Mental Illness </b>   <b data-is-speakable>Over the years, six of the Galvins' 12 children were diagnosed with schizophrenia. Robert Kolker, who has a new book on the family, says "there is a lot of hope and inspiration in this story."</b>
